metadata.name: EOF 015
metadata.description:
No one clearly remembers
                                    the end–
It is the good parts that come back
to the memory unscathed.
 
The nostalgia kicks in,
We reminisce when things were “better”,
            when we needed more than a virtual click
                        to create something heartfelt and real.
 
But what about the end?
What about the residu…
            and what about what follows?
 
Can we find beauty in
            the unclear / the unknown?

The End of Film is a series of photos exploring that last image that sneaks partly onto the film roll. The title of the series equivocally refers to the increasing obsolescence of analog photography.

edition 1/1

5961x7680 pixels
300 dpi
